The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Top cop to flag off meet 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Renowned runners from all over the country are likely to take part in the Airtel Calcutta Marathon organised by The Telegraph and the Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) in association with the Athletic Coaches? Association of Bengal. The event will be flagged off on March 13 by the Commissioner of Police Prasun Mukherjee, who is also the chairman of the tournament?s working committee. 

The runners will have to cover a total distance of 42.360 km (men 42.195km, women 10.500km and open 4.200km). US Consul General George Sibley will take part for the 10-km stretch. 

Former players, school children, celebrities from the entertainment world and common people are also expected to take part. 

Footballers ? P. K. Banerjee, Pradip Choudhary, Chief Minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, Sheriff Chuni Goswami, Governor Gopal Gandhi, Lt general Arvind Sharma, GOC-in-charge, Eastern Command, tennis coach Akhtar Ali will also be present on the day. 




